com.tibco.tea.agent.support

Class TeaIllegalArgumentException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.tibco.tea.agent.support.TeaException
            • com.tibco.tea.agent.support.TeaIllegalArgumentException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class TeaIllegalArgumentException
extends TeaException
    Exception to indicate a bad parameter for TeaOperation . The exception will be interpreted as a validation error and the messages for the parameters will be displayed in the UI form or shell. The object state should not change when this exception is thrown.The HTTP status code used for indicating this exception is 400.
